### Affected Version of Concrete CMS

9.x

### Description

So i want to divide my users up into usergroups but i cant seem to make the automation work. To start off my CC install is not open for users to register themself, this is done by an admin. The users emailadres is what i wish to filter on since that determines if they gets put in a usergroup

i followed this tutorial but i cant get it to work
https://documentation.concretecms.org/developers/users-groups/groups/advanced-automated-groups

i made the usergroup through the dashboard, ticked the 
This group is automatically entered.
When the "Check Automated Groups" Job runs.

i made this file: 
/application/src/User/Group/AutomatedGroup/GroupOne.php

with this code:
`
namespace application\src\User\Group\AutomatedGroup;

use Concrete\Core\User\User;
use Concrete\Core\User\UserInfo;
use Concrete\Core\User\Group\GroupAutomationController;

class GroupOne extends GroupAutomationController {
    public function check(User $ux)
    {
        $userID = $ux->getUserID();
        $ui = UserInfo::getByID($userID);
        if ($ui) {
            $email = $ui->getUserEmail();
            echo $email; // Debug: Output the user's email
            if (str_contains($email, '@groupone.com')) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
`

I can run the automation, it goes through my users but no dividing up.

### How to reproduce

see above

